Vocalization_type: contact call between males and females, editorial comments by Theodore Parker II
file.name: XC406290-MontezumaandTed.mp3
Remarks:
Recording of contact calls between males and females, described as a "conversation" among the birds.  Advertising call.  Appended to the recording is a conversation among Theodore Parker III, Mickey Willis, and myself discussing the first part of this same recording.  Ted, Mickey and I were listening to this recording in my parents' living room in Baton Rouge, Louisiana, while I recorded our conversation discussing it.  I was explaining certain things to Mickey, and Ted was explaining certain things to both Mickey and myself. 

The recording was made using a Marantz tape cassette recorder and a Sennheiser electret microphone, by a stream under a large tree, where several birds were perched and hopping around.  I have long been fascinated by the fairy-like voices of the birds on this recording, who were conversing and occasionally erupting into the famous, explosive song of the Icterid.
